31#include "mech_locl.h"
32
33GSSAPI_LIB_FUNCTION OM_uint32 GSSAPI_LIB_CALL
34gss_import_sec_context(OM_uint32 *minor_status,
35 const gss_buffer_t interprocess_token,
36 gss_ctx_id_t *context_handle)
37{
38 OM_uint32 major_status;
39 gssapi_mech_interface m;
40 struct _gss_context *ctx;
41 gss_OID_desc mech_oid;
42 gss_buffer_desc buf;
43 unsigned char *p;
44 size_t len;
45
46 *minor_status = 0;
47 *context_handle = GSS_C_NO_CONTEXT;
48
49 /*
50 * We added an oid to the front of the token in
51 * gss_export_sec_context.
52 */
53 p = interprocess_token->value;
54 len = interprocess_token->length;
55 if (len < 2)
56 return (GSS_S_DEFECTIVE_TOKEN);
57 mech_oid.length = (p[0] << 8) | p[1];
58 if (len < mech_oid.length + 2)
59 return (GSS_S_DEFECTIVE_TOKEN);
60 mech_oid.elements = p + 2;
61 buf.length = len - 2 - mech_oid.length;
62 buf.value = p + 2 + mech_oid.length;
63
64 m = __gss_get_mechanism(&mech_oid);
65 if (!m)
66 return (GSS_S_DEFECTIVE_TOKEN);
67
68 ctx = malloc(sizeof(struct _gss_context));
69 if (!ctx) {
70 *minor_status = ENOMEM;
71 return (GSS_S_FAILURE);
72 }
73 ctx->gc_mech = m;
74 major_status = m->gm_import_sec_context(minor_status,
75 &buf, &ctx->gc_ctx);
76 if (major_status != GSS_S_COMPLETE) {
77 _gss_mg_error(m, major_status, *minor_status);
78 free(ctx);
79 } else {
80 *context_handle = (gss_ctx_id_t) ctx;
81 }
82
83 return (major_status);
84}
